-- 
Exxon Torrance, California, Plant Reports Unplanned Flaring

-- B y   P a u l   B u r k h a r d t
-- 
2011-03-24T16:25:23Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-24/exxon-torrance-california-refinery-reports-unplanned-flaring.html
Exxon Mobil Corp. (XOM)  reported flaring
at its Torrance, California, refinery starting today at 8:05
a.m. local time, according to a filing with regulators.  The event is expected to last until 10 a.m., Exxon said in
the filing to the  South Coast Air Quality Management District .  Flaring at the 155,800-barrel-a-day plant had no impact on
production, according to a separate filing with the California
Emergency Management Agency.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Paul Burkhardt in New York at 
 pburkhardt@bloomberg.net ;  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Dan Stets at 
 dstets@bloomberg.net . 